Anthrax - Azerbaijan
--------------------
Information received on 7 Aug 2019 from Dr. Galib Abdulaliyev, Head, CVO, Animal Health Department, Azerbaijan Food Safety Agency, Baku, Azerbaijan

Summary:
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 1 Aug 2019
Date of confirmation of the event: 6 Aug 2019
Report date: 7 Aug 2019
Date submitted to OIE: 7 Aug 2019
Reason for notification: Recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 3 Jun 2013
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis _
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak Location: Aghjabedi (Aghjabedi, Aghjabedi)
Date of start of the outbreak: 1 Aug 2019
Outbreak Status: Continuing (date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Total animals affected / Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Sheep / 140 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Sheep / 0.71 / 0.71 / 100 / 0.71
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak(s); quarantine; official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste; disinfection; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type: Central Veterinary Laboratory at the Azerbaijan Food Safety Institute (National laboratory)
Tests and results
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Sheep / bacteriological examination / 6 Aug 2019 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

